        'onboarding.waiver_intro': 'PLEASE READ CAREFULLY. THIS IS A LEGAL DOCUMENT THAT AFFECTS YOUR LEGAL RIGHTS.',
        'onboarding.waiver_text': 'This Participation Agreement, Release and Waiver of Liability (“Agreement”) is entered into by the undersigned individual (“Participant”), in favor of North Plains Volunteer Network (“NPVN”) and the North Plains Senior Center (“NPSC”), each an Oregon nonprofit organization, and each of their respective directors, officers, employees, contractors, volunteers, partners, affiliates, and agents (collectively, the “Released Parties”).\n\nBy creating an account with NPVN, volunteering, receiving services, or participating in any activity coordinated, referred, promoted, or facilitated by NPVN, Participant agrees as follows:\n\n1. Nature of the Organizations and Services\n\nParticipant understands and agrees that:\n\nNPVN is a volunteer coordination and referral organization only\n\nNPSC is a community organization that may serve as a host site, referral partner, or community collaborator, but does not supervise or control volunteers or clients connected through NPVN\n\nNeither NPVN nor NPSC supervises, directs, controls, employs, or guarantees the conduct of volunteers, service recipients, or third parties\n\nActivities may occur at private residences, public locations, NPSC facilities, or other third-party sites not owned or controlled by NPVN.\n\n2. Voluntary Participation and Assumption of Risk\n\nParticipant voluntarily chooses to participate in activities associated with NPVN and/or NPSC and understands that such participation may involve risks, including but not limited to:\n\nPersonal injury, illness, or death\n\nProperty damage or loss\n\nAccidents during travel or transportation\n\nEnvironmental or site-specific hazards\n\nInteractions with other participants or third parties\n\nParticipant knowingly, freely, and expressly assumes all risks, whether known or unknown, foreseeable or unforeseeable, arising from participation.\n\n3. Release and Waiver of Liability\n\nTo the fullest extent permitted by Oregon law, Participant hereby releases, waives, discharges, and holds harmless the Released Parties from any and all claims, demands, damages, losses, costs, or liabilities of any kind, whether arising in tort, contract, statute, or otherwise, including but not limited to claims for:\n\nPersonal injury\n\nIllness or medical conditions\n\nProperty damage or loss\n\nEmotional distress\n\nWrongful death\n\nThis release applies even if caused in whole or in part by the ordinary negligence of any Released Party. This release does not apply to intentional misconduct or gross negligence to the extent prohibited by law.\n\n4. Mutual Release Between Volunteers and Service Recipients\n\nParticipant acknowledges that volunteers and service recipients interact directly with one another and that neither NPVN nor NPSC controls those interactions.\n\nParticipant agrees to release, waive, and hold harmless NPVN, NPSC, and other participants from claims arising out of such interactions, except in cases of intentional misconduct or gross negligence.\n\n5. Premises and Facilities (Including North Plains Senior Center)\n\nParticipant understands and agrees that:\n\nParticipation may occur at NPSC facilities, private homes, or other third-party locations\n\nNeither NPVN nor NPSC guarantees the safety, condition, or suitability of any premises\n\nParticipant assumes all risks associated with entering and remaining on such premises\n\n6. Medical Care and Insurance\n\nParticipant understands that neither NPVN nor NPSC:\n\nProvides medical, health, accident, disability, or liability insurance\n\nAssumes responsibility for medical treatment or related costs\n\nParticipant is solely responsible for securing insurance coverage and for all medical expenses incurred.\n\nIn the event of an emergency, Participant authorizes reasonable efforts to obtain emergency medical care and releases the Released Parties from liability related to such efforts.\n\n7. Transportation Provided by Volunteers\n\nParticipant understands and agrees that transportation assistance may be requested or provided through NPVN-connected activities.\n\nParticipant further understands and agrees that:\n\nAny transportation is voluntarily provided by individual volunteers, not by NPVN or NPSC\n\nNPVN and NPSC do not own, operate, maintain, inspect, supervise, or insure any vehicle used in connection with volunteer activities\n\nNPVN and NPSC do not verify driver licensure, driving history, vehicle condition, or insurance coverage\n\nAll transportation arrangements are made directly between participants, and participation is entirely voluntary\n\nEach Participant agrees that they are solely responsible for their own safety and for complying with all applicable laws, including maintaining valid licensure and insurance where required.\n\nTo the fullest extent permitted by Oregon law, Participant assumes all risks associated with providing or receiving transportation, including but not limited to accidents, injuries, property damage, delays, or losses, and releases and holds harmless NPVN and NPSC from any claims arising out of or related to transportation activities.\n\n8. Conduct and Responsibility\n\nParticipant agrees to:\n\nAct lawfully and respectfully\n\nFollow posted rules and reasonable safety guidance\n\nImmediately report unsafe conditions\n\nNPVN and NPSC reserve the right to suspend or terminate participation at their discretion.\n\n9. Media Release (Optional but Strongly Recommended)\n\nParticipant grants NPVN and NPSC permission to use photographs, video, or audio recordings taken in connection with activities for lawful promotional, educational, or reporting purposes, without compensation.\n\n10. Minors\n\nParticipants under 18 years of age may only participate with written consent of a parent or legal guardian, who agrees to all terms of this Agreement on the minor’s behalf.\n\n11. Governing Law and Severability\n\nThis Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of Oregon. If any provision is held invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.\n\n12. Acknowledgment and Acceptance\n\nBy creating an account, signing electronically, or participating in any activity associated with NPVN or NPSC, Participant confirms that they:\n\nHave read and understand this Agreement\n\nUnderstand they are waiving certain legal rights\n\nAgree voluntarily and knowingly to all terms',
